The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
Archives
				 Cracker arrests
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Nov. 9: Over 500 people were arrested across the city on Diwali night for bursting banned crackers.																								If central Calcutta was noisy, Ballygunge Circular Road was no better.																								Rooftop revellers and those in silence zones were a major problem, said Biswajit Mukherjee, a senior law officer of the environment department and member-secretary of the noise monitoring committee who was in a team that went around the city. 																								The major offenders were from central Calcutta, said police commissioner Gautam Mohan Chakrabarti. Two arrests were made from highrises in Ballygunge. 																								A man was caught inside NRS Medical College and Hospital and another outside Sambhunath Pandit Hospital																								Environment activist Subhas Dutta said tonight was ear-shattering.
